<h2>10. User Roles &amp; Permissions</h2>
<table>
  <thead>
    <tr>
      <th>Role</th>
      <th>Permissions</th>
      <th>Access</th>
    </tr>
  </thead>
  <tbody>
    <tr>
      <td>Applicant / Student</td>
      <td>Build profile, apply to jobs, view applications, edit profile.</td>
      <td>Public / Authenticated</td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
      <td>Recruiter / Employer</td>
      <td>Create and manage job listings, review applicants, manage listings.</td>
      <td>Recruiter Only</td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
      <td>Admin</td>
      <td>Approve/reject jobs, manage users, view metrics, moderate content.</td>
      <td>Admin Only</td>
    </tr>
  </tbody>
</table>

<h2>11. Login &amp; Logout</h2>
<p>Authentication is handled by Supabase via <code>src/lib/supabase.ts</code>. Users sign in from the Auth page at <code>/[locale]/auth</code>.</p>
<ul>
  <li><strong>Login:</strong> Enter credentials or use configured social/login providers. The user receives a valid session token.</li>
  <li><strong>Logout:</strong> The logout flow clears the session and redirects to the public landing page or login screen.</li>
  <li><strong>Session handling:</strong> Auth state is maintained in the client and protected routes require a valid session.</li>
</ul>

<h2>12. Dashboards Overview</h2>
<p>The application surfaces different dashboard experiences based on user role.</p>
<table>
  <thead>
    <tr>
      <th>Dashboard</th>
      <th>Primary View</th>
      <th>Key Features</th>
    </tr>
  </thead>
  <tbody>
    <tr>
      <td>Student Dashboard</td>
      <td><code>src/views/StudentDashboard.tsx</code></td>
      <td>Application tracker, saved jobs, profile progress, and recent activity.</td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
      <td>Recruiter Dashboard</td>
      <td><code>src/views/RecruiterDashboard.tsx</code></td>
      <td>Post jobs, review applicants, manage listings, and view recruiter stats.</td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
      <td>Admin Dashboard</td>
      <td><code>src/app/[locale]/admin</code></td>
      <td>Moderate jobs, manage users, approve posts, and monitor platform health.</td>
    </tr>
  </tbody>
</table>

<h2>13. Security Guidelines</h2>
<ul>
  <li>Do not expose <code>SUPABASE_SERVICE_ROLE_KEY</code> to the client. Keep it in server-only environment variables.</li>
  <li>Use role-based access checks for admin and recruiter pages.</li>
  <li>Validate all API requests server-side before modifying database state.</li>
  <li>Store only necessary user data and avoid saving sensitive information in logs.</li>
  <li>Rotate Supabase service keys regularly and revoke compromised keys immediately.</li>
</ul>

<h2>14. Troubleshooting</h2>
<h3>Common issues</h3>
<ul>
  <li><strong>Blank pages or build errors:</strong> Run <code>npm run build</code> locally to catch compile-time issues.</li>
  <li><strong>Auth failures:</strong> Ensure Supabase keys and <code>NEXTAUTH_URL</code> match the app URL exactly.</li>
  <li><strong>Missing translations:</strong> Confirm the JSON keys exist for the current route and locale in <code>src/messages</code>.</li>
  <li><strong>Admin panel not visible:</strong> Verify the authenticated user has the correct admin role and refresh after login.</li>
</ul>

<h3>Diagnostics &amp; quick checks</h3>
<ul>
  <li><code>npm run dev</code> — start local development.</li>
  <li><code>npm run build</code> — validate production build and catch errors.</li>
  <li><code>npm run lint</code> — identify syntax and style issues when configured.</li>
  <li>Use browser dev tools to inspect API calls, network failures, and translation loading.</li>
</ul>

<h2>15. FAQ</h2>
<table>
  <thead>
    <tr>
      <th>Question</th>
      <th>Answer</th>
    </tr>
  </thead>
  <tbody>
    <tr>
      <td>How do I add a new locale?</td>
      <td>Create a folder under <code>src/app</code>, add translations under <code>src/messages</code>, and update <code>src/i18n/navigation.ts</code>.</td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
      <td>Why is the admin page not visible?</td>
      <td>Admin features are shown only to users with the admin role. Check the user's role in the database and refresh after login.</td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
      <td>Where are recruiter job postings stored?</td>
      <td>Job postings are stored in the <code>jobs</code> table and linked to recruiters by the <code>owner_id</code>.</td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
      <td>Why does Supabase auth redirect incorrectly?</td>
      <td>Verify <code>NEXTAUTH_URL</code> in <code>.env.local</code> matches your site URL and ensure the redirect URI is allowed in Supabase Auth settings.</td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
      <td>Can I deploy Connekt outside Vercel?</td>
      <td>Yes. Any Next.js App Router-compatible host works, but keep the service role key secure on the server.</td>
    </tr>
  </tbody>
</table>

<h2>16. Glossary</h2>
<table>
  <thead>
    <tr>
      <th>Term</th>
      <th>Definition</th>
    </tr>
  </thead>
  <tbody>
    <tr>
      <td>App Router</td>
      <td>Next.js routing system for server and client components in <code>src/app</code>.</td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
      <td>Locale</td>
      <td>Language-specific route prefix, such as <code>/en</code> or <code>/fr</code>.</td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
      <td>Supabase</td>
      <td>Backend-as-a-service platform used for authentication, database, and storage.</td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
      <td>Service Role Key</td>
      <td>Privileged Supabase key used only on the server for admin-level operations.</td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
      <td>Recruiter</td>
      <td>User role that can publish job postings and review applicants.</td>
    </tr>
  </tbody>
</table>

